sec.p:
Genes previously reported to be of importance between phenotypes with alternative reproductive strategies in fish are here termed ‘candidate genes’ in the context of social dominance. The sequences of the candidate genes gnrh (gonadotropin releasing hormone receptor;
[14,19]), epd (ependymin;
[68]), avp (arginine vasopressin;
[22,48,55,69]), somatostatin[14], egr1 (early growth response protein,
[19]), galn (galanin,
[14]) and cyp19a1 (brain aromatase enzyme,
[14]) were blasted (BLASTn) against the de novo assembly contigs using BLAST 2 sequence in NCBI to confirm their presence in the reference transcriptome and evaluate its differential expression among phenotypes.
